                            <comment id="17413882" author="taroplus" created="Mon, 13 Sep 2021 03:16:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/spark/blob/master/sql/catalyst/src/main/scala/org/apache/spark/sql/catalyst/expressions/SchemaPruning.scala#L69&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/spark/blob/master/sql/catalyst/src/main/scala/org/apache/spark/sql/catalyst/expressions/SchemaPruning.scala#L69&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;often time (as long as I observed), left struct and the right struct are the same one. And every call to&#160;&lt;tt&gt;StructType.fieldNames&lt;/tt&gt;&#160; runs &lt;tt&gt;&#160;fields.map(_.name).&#160;&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;this computation is quite expensive for 10K fields.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;&#160;val filteredRightFieldNames = rightStruct.fieldNames&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;tt&gt;&#160; &#160; .filter(name =&amp;gt; leftStruct.fieldNames.exists(resolver(_, name)))&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;tt&gt;&#160;&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
